==English==

===Etymology===
Middle English ''[[tymber]]'', from Old English ''timber'', from common Germanic ''*timram'', derived from Proto-Indo-European ''*dem(H₂)-'', build, house.  Near cognates include German ''[[Zimmer]]'', room (the original sense being seen in the derivative ''[[Zimmermann]]'', carpenter), Old Icelandic ''[[timbr]]'', and Gothic ''[[̹̼̰̈́͂̾̽]]'' (timrjan) to build.

